snippet.textDisplay:
12:36 I posted this earlier, but as you guys did not review 'em, I am reposting: You really need to explore Dhoom, which is way better than Ambala. You guys should check out all of the “Dhoom” movies. They are about thieves and robberies. General audiences particularly liked the second one amongst the three (Dhoom 2). That’s why I’m sharing the robbery scenes from the second one—some fantastic CGIs (in 2006/2007 Bollywood perspective).
Please check out:

https://youtu.be/3bMYgo_S0Kc

https://youtu.be/l5ZiW3mCuE4

https://youtu.be/fmKWuAVt1vI

https://youtu.be/hNg1ksFeyv0

You guy should checkout the other two movies, too. The third one especially had lots of CGIs in it.
Watch the making (Dhoom 3 was filmed in Chicago actually)
https://youtu.be/0LgpV4FPYB4

Some final cut examples:
https://youtu.be/1yPakqFjL5Y

Hope you have a good watch. In fact, try to watch some of the Dhoom movies with subtitles, if you guys like the scenes.
